THIS PROJECT INCLUDES PROVIDING A NEW, COMPLETE FIRE ALARM SYSTEM FOR THE NEW MARRIOTT
HEADQUARTERS HOTEL. THE SYSTEM CONSISTS OF MAIN FIRE ALARM CONTROL PANEL (XLSV2), FOUR
REMOTE FIRE ALARM CONTROL PANELS (XLSRV2-1 - XLSRV2-4), A GRAPHIC ANNUNCIATOR, EQUIPMENT
CONTROL/STATUS PANEL, ADDRESSABLE SMOKE, HEAT, AND DUCT DETECTORS, MANUAL PULL STATIONS,
ADDRESSABLE INTERFACE MODULES, AUDIO/VISUAL DEVICES (SPEAKER/STROBES,SPEAKERS, STROBES),
NOTIFICATION APPLIANCE EXTENDER PANELS (PAD-4), AND AREA OF REFUGE SYSTEM. THIS SYSTEM WILL
BE NETWORKED TO THE MARRIOTT OFFICE BUILDING FIRE ALARM SYSTEM, SUBMITTED UNDER SEPARATE
COVER AS SIEMENS PROJECT 44OP-258034. PROVISIONS HAVE BEEN MADE FOR SENDING LIVE VOICE
MESSAGES TO AND RECEIVING FROM MARRIOTT OFFICE BUILDING (HEADQUARTERS). THE NETWORK
CIRCUITS WILL BE WIRED CLASS X. SIGNALING LINE CIRCUITS WILL BE WIRED CLASS A, AND NOTIFICATION
APPLIANCE CIRCUITS WILL BE WIRED CLASS B.
THE SYSTEM HAS BEEN DESIGNED PER SPECIFICATIONS (28 31 00, IFC, DATED MARCH 29, 2019) AND
CONTRACT DRAWINGS (H-E0.01 THROUGH H-E7.06, REVISION 7.1, DATED 7/17/19) ISSUED BY DEWBERRY.
NO CHANGES HAVE BEEN MADE TO THE ENGINEER OF RECORD'S DESIGN EXCEPT AS NECESSARY FOR
PRODUCT APPLICATION.
